  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Social Work Associate",
  "description": "<p><strong>Social Work Associate</strong></p><p>Working Hours: Monday – Friday (9am – 6pm)<br />Location: Buangkok<br />Salary: $2600 - $2900</p><p>Social Work Associate will be working with the youths staying in an institutional facility, which focus on community rehabilitation.<br /><br /><strong>List of responsibilities, but not limited to:</strong></p><p><strong>Programme management</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct needs assessment to develop suitable programmes, developing risk assessment and manage risks involved in programmes</li><li>Plan for, lead and facilitate programmes</li><li>Implement appropriate assessment tools to develop and evaluate group work outcomes</li><li>Develop and plan group processes and specialised intervention strategies</li><li>Facilitate, evaluate and review therapeutic group work sessions</li></ul><p><strong>Volunteer management</strong></p><ul><li>Volunteer management and engagement.</li><li>Sourcing for volunteer partners to value add to hostel programmes</li></ul><p><strong>Casework support</strong></p><ul><li>Support case management, include preparing, and attending all necessary case-related appointments/meetings</li><li>Develop / maintain good working relationship with stakeholders, including parents and schools</li><li>Apply restorative practices including planning and facilitating a restorative circle and principles of trauma-informed care</li></ul><p><strong>Administrative</strong></p><ul><li>Able to organize and upkeep documents</li><li>Able to keep to administrative timelines</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Social Work with prior experience of mentoring and working with youths.</li><li>Prior experience in working with youth-at-risk would be an advantage.</li></ul><p><strong>Tee Xin Li Reg No: R24121619</strong><br /><strong>The Supreme Hr Advisory Pte Ltd EA No: 14C7279</strong></p>",
